guru_ruvllm-complete_593.content:
RuvLLM supports federated learning for distributed, privacy-preserving training:

```rust
pub struct FederatedCoordinator {
    agents: Vec<AgentHandle>,
    aggregation_strategy: AggregationStrategy,
    privacy_budget: PrivacyBudget,
    round_config: RoundConfig,
}

pub struct EphemeralAgent {
    local_model: Model,
    local_data: DataBuffer,
    differential_privacy: DPMechanism,
}

impl FederatedCoordinator {
    /// Run one federated learning round
    pub async fn run_round(&mut self) -> RoundResult {
        // 1. Broadcast current global model
        let global_weights = self.global_model.get_weights();
        for agent in &self.agents {
            agent.receive_weights(&global_weights).await;
        }

        // 2. Local training (parallel)
        let updates: Vec<_> = futures::future::join_all(
            self.agents.iter().map(|a| a.train_local())
        ).await;

        // 3. Secure aggregation
        let aggregated = self.aggregation_strategy.aggregate(&updates);

        // 4. Update global model
        self.global_model.apply_update(aggregated);

        RoundResult { /* ... */ }
    }
}

impl EphemeralAgent {
    /// Local training with differential privacy
    pub async fn train_local(&self) -> ModelUpdate {
        let mut update = ModelUpdate::zeros_like(&self.local_model);

        for batch in self.local_data.iter() {
            let loss = self.local_model.forward(&batch);
            let grads = loss.backward();

            // Clip gradients for DP
            let clipped = self.differential_privacy.clip_gradients(&grads);
            update.accumulate(&clipped);
        }

        // Add noise for differential privacy
        self.differential_privacy.add_noise(&mut update);

        update
    }
}
```

**Aggregation Strategies:**

| Strategy | Description | Use Case |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| FedAvg | Weighted average by data size | IID data |
| FedProx | Proximal term for heterogeneity | Non-IID data |
| FedMA | Model averaging with matching | Architecture variations |
| SecAgg | Secure aggregation (MPC) | Privacy-critical |

